{
  "stem": "1581.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was Franz Joseph I, and later on, Karl.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And of course, we followed the events of World War I, as far as I can remember, very closely.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The life was not bad at all.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "However, there was always a creeping anti-Semitism all over middle Europe, and particularly Eastern Europe.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had-- as far as I remember-- no bad experiences, as far as this is concerned, until the end of the war, when there was a short period without law and order.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was no government established yet in the new Czech Republic.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was a real murderous pogrom which cost us our lives.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I-- I very vividly remember that there was-- I was a little over-- over seven years old.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was shooting and-- and yelling.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father grabbed me out of the bed in the middle of the night, and we went up to the attic of our house to hide from these hordes that invaded every Jewish house.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As we later learned, two Jews were shot during the-- and killed during the pogrom.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was quite horrifying, because we heard them plundering the place and robbing everything that was in sight.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then they were talking about putting the house on fire, which of course would have been our end.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But then, they thought better of it, or they were chased away.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And after many hours of anguish, we went back to our place to find it in shambles.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was not a drawer that wasn't emptied out, and the whole place was just ruined.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So as we were in our night gowns and with a winter coat over it, my father took me to the railroad, and we went to Vienna.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
